			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Don&#39;t see an appropriate job on our jobs page, but still want to reach out and introduce yourself? This is why we&#39;ve created the &quot;other&quot; job post. We&#39;d like to meet you too.</p>
<p>
Lullabot is a talent agency. We&#39;re always looking for passionate, talented, and quick-witted people to help us do awesome things. We&#39;re known for being down-to-earth, trustworthy, hardworking, creative, friendly, and deeply knowledgeable. Most of employees work from home, yet we have a tightly-knit team which works very closely together despite geographical separation.</p>
<p>
More than anything, we&#39;re driven by wanting to do interesting and challenging work &ndash; and to do it well. This has taken us in many unexpected and exciting directions over the years. We&#39;ve grown the scope of our <a href="http://www.lullabot.com/what-we-do">services</a>; we&#39;ve built several products; we&#39;ve worked on some amazing projects with some amazing <a href="http://www.lullabot.com/work">clients</a>; and we&#39;ve been happy to learn and explore. We never quite know where the future is going to take us. Think you&#39;d like to be part of our future? Introduce yourself.</p>
<p>
One thing that we say is that &quot;we tend to hire more for the person than the position.&quot; Although we often have specific resource needs, we try to find talented and driven people who are a match for Lullabot&#39;s culture. Often if we can find the right people, we&#39;ll spend some time to figure out how to incorporate them into our work.</p>
<p>
Even though we may not have a specific position posted, we&#39;re always on the lookout for great designers, marketing people, front-end and back-end developers, mobile developers, project managers, content and community strategists, sales and account management people, and even business development, accounting, administrative staff, and &quot;others&quot;. What do you do? Think you&#39;ve got a talent that we should be interested in? Get on our radar!</p>
<p>
<strong>Some things to know before you apply:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Take a look at our <a href="http://www.lullabot.com/values">core values</a>. They act as our guiding principals and are very important to us. If they don&#39;t resonate with you, you might not be a good match for Lullabot.</li>
<li>
With a few exceptions, most &#39;bots end up doing a lot of traveling. You okay with at least one week of travel every 2 months?</li>
<li>
As a distributed company, we require excellent communicators. You&#39;ll need to have excellent verbal and written skills.</li>
<li>
We also need self-starters who are good at managing their own tasks and time. There is no such thing as micromanagement at a distributed company. No one will be looking over your shoulder. It&#39;ll be up to you to get your work done and communicated about it effectively.</li>
<li>
You&#39;ll find that most of the &#39;bots are pretty quick-witted with a good sense of humor. We can do some high pressure work and the ability to maintain optimism and laugh it off can be a necessity.</li>
<li>
We ask people to create a 2 minute video to submit with their application. Since we don&#39;t tend to do in-person interviews, this is a great way to &quot;meet you&quot; and has become an essential part of our hiring process. We realize that most people are a bit nervous and self-conscious recording a video of themselves and we certainly take that into account. It does&#39;t need to be high production value either. You can take a video with your smartphone and put it on YouTube (usually unlisted) or Vimeo (usually password protected). Your resume and cover letter will tell us about your work experience. Use the video to tell us about yourself. The video is not required, but we watch and appreciate every video submitted. It is *very rare* for us to hire anyone who hasn&#39;t submitted a video and whom we don&#39;t already know. Here are the video applications from several of the bots who were hired: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fC4pL193fVw">Seth</a>, <a href="http://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/1771736/Video/James%20Sansbury.m4v">James</a>, <a href="https://vimeo.com/26632559">Joe</a>, <a href="https://vimeo.com/60512806">Olanda</a>, <a href="http://www.godbolt.me/lullabot/">Micah</a>. Have fun with it!</li>
</ul>
