			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Technical Project Manager</strong></p>
<p>
<br />
Have that rare combination of technical acumen and the ability to lead teams, make decisions, and get things done? We&rsquo;d love to talk to you about managing projects for Lullabot! Lullabot makes hyper-aesthetic, epic-scale web projects successful for companies like Martha Stewart, NBC Universal, Turner Broadcasting, The Recording Academy, Intel, and the Pac12, and that&rsquo;s just our work over the last 6 months. Projects of this magnitude require a competent hand on the tiller&mdash;someone technical enough to understand the intricacies of large-scale Drupal web projects, but also someone that can see the big picture, translating business goals into requirements, specs into estimates and tickets, and talented individuals into teams. With that in mind, Lullabot is hiring an experienced technical project manager.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities include: writing requirements as specifications, user stories, or tickets; and managing scope, deliverables, schedules, and team resources for Lullabot client and internal projects. Daily tasks include leading daily 15 minute check-in calls for each project, scheduling and leading periodic sprint reviews and planning meetings, tending the ticket queue and managing task lists, communicating (email/phone) with clients, performing rigorous testing and verification, and keeping projects on track and moving forward. In addition, we believe a great project manager should have experience doing the work that they&#39;re managing. Experience as a front-end or Drupal developer is a huge plus. &nbsp;Lullabot is a distributed company without a central office, so like all Lullabot jobs, this is a telecommuting position that occasionally involves travel.</p>
<p>
Additional responsibilities include helping to write and assemble new project proposals and statements of work, estimating and staffing projects, meeting with clients, pursuing and growing development partnerships, and coordinating project launches.</p>
<p>
If this sounds like a lot, it is. But Lullabot is a very collaborative company so you won&#39;t be working in isolation. You&#39;ll be working with a team of highly experienced Drupal consultants and developers with excellent communication skills and a passion for their work.</p>
<p>
<strong>Ideal candidates should:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Have 2 years or more experience managing or participating on large-scale Drupal projects.</li>
<li>
Have experience managing projects in ticketing systems such as Github, Assembla, JIRA, or Unfuddle.</li>
<li>
Understand code promotion workflows, version control, and development best practices.</li>
<li>
Be a great communicator with good writing skills.</li>
<li>
Be comfortable managing and organizing remote virtual teams.</li>
<li>
Be based in the U.S.</li>
<li>
Have a great sense of humor!</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Availability: </strong>Ideally, we&rsquo;d like to hire a full-time resource, but we&rsquo;re open to accomplished contractors as well.</p>
<p>
<strong>Apply:&nbsp;</strong>We&#39;re asking applicants to submit a 2-minute video introducing themselves. We realize that for many people this is an exercise in self-consciousness, however, being a distributed company, it helps us quickly get to know you. Just shoot something with your computer&#39;s webcam and post it as a password-protected video on Vimeo. You can post your video elsewhere, or get more fancy with it if you like, but we&#39;re really just looking for a brief introduction. Take a look at one of these videos to see what&#39;s gotten folks hired in the past.</p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>About Lullabot:</strong>Lullabot is a small Drupal-oriented consulting, training, and development company which has provided technical architecture, guided development, and helped launch many of Drupal&#39;s top sites including those by The Grammys, Martha Stewart, Sony Music, IBM, O&#39;Reilly Media, Lifetime Television, Fast Company, MTV UK, Harvard University, Walmart, the BBC, Verizon, the Washington Post, and more.</p>
]]></description>
